<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Introduction to CSS</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: sans-serif;
      margin: 2rem;
      background-color: #f9f9f9;
      color: #333;
    }
    h1 {
      color: #e91e63;
    }
    code {
      background-color: #eee;
      padding: 0.1rem 0.3rem;
      border-radius: 4px;
    }
    a {
      color: #e91e63;
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>What is CSS?</h1>
  <p>CSS stands for <strong>Cascading Style Sheets</strong>. It's used to style HTML elements.</p>

  <h2>Basic CSS Properties</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><code>color</code> – text color</li>
    <li><code>background-color</code> – background color</li>
    <li><code>font-size</code> – size of text</li>
    <li><code>margin</code> – space outside an element</li>
    <li><code>padding</code> – space inside an element</li>
  </ul>

  <p>CSS makes your page look good!</p>

  <p><a href="html.html">← Back to HTML Page</a></p>
</body>
</html>
